Vice President Biden spoke with Dr. Ayad Allawi, former Iraqi Prime Minister and leader of the Iraqiyya coalition, about the status of Iraqi negotiations on the formation of a new government. The Vice President emphasized the goal of an inclusive government that reflects the results of the election and stated that the United States is not backing specific candidates. He expressed support for power-sharing arrangements in accordance with the constitution and urged Dr. Allawi and other Iraqi leaders to expedite efforts to form a government that addresses the needs of the Iraqi people.